FBIS4-18140 "drweu062_j_94003" FBIS-WEU-94-062 Daily Report 30 Mar 1994 ITALY & VATICAN CITY Confident of Forming Government Confident of Forming Government LD3003175994 Rome RAI Televideo Teletext in Italian 1702 GMT 30 Mar 94 LD3003175994 Rome RAI Televideo Teletext Italian BFN [Text] "We will form a government and do so soon," Silvio Berlusconi said today, following his first [postelection] meeting with Umberto Bossi. Berlusconi said they will meet again on Friday [1 April], adding, "There is a very friendly climate. We are on the right road." Bossi and Roberto Maroni also thought the meeting was "very positive." Bossi said: "We spoke, we started to thrash things out, and, if everything goes as it should, we will be able to give the country a government soon."
